<p>Putting images on the web is a balance between quality and disc space. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The bigger images not only take more storage but that increased size will take longer to load, decreasing customer satisfaction. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>PNG is is lossless compression file type: Better for graphics, cartoons, or illustrations. storing line drawings, text, and iconic graphics at a small file size.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>JPEG is better for actual photos that need to be compressed. Lossy compressed file format. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>GIF</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

